trans-unit.source: A literal expression stores the code of an expression as a literal code fragment.
trans-unit.target: En litteral uttrykket lagrer koden for et uttrykk som en litteral code-fragment.

trans-unit.source: The CodeDOM does not translate literal code fragments.
Literal code fragments are stored and output just as they are.
trans-unit.target: Litteralen kodefragmenter lagres, og sender slik de er.

trans-unit.source: CodeDOM objects that contain literal code are provided so developers can encapsulate code that is already in the target language.
trans-unit.target: CodeDOM objekter som inneholder litteral kode er angitt slik at utviklere kan omfatter kode som allerede finnes p책 spr책ket som m책l.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeSnippetExpression.Value%2A> property contains the literal code for this snippet expression.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeSnippetExpression.Value%2A>egenskapen inneholder litteral koden for dette uttrykket kodesnutt.</xref:System.CodeDom.CodeSnippetExpression.Value%2A>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeSnippetExpression"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeSnippetExpression"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeSnippetExpression"></xref> class using the specified literal expression.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeSnippetExpression"> </xref> klasse ved hjelp av det angitte Litteralen uttrykket.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the literal string of code.
This can contain code or comments.
trans-unit.target: Dette kan inneholde kode eller kommentarer.
